  "recipe": {
    "description": "Marinate thin strips of pork first in a mixture of soy sauce, a little sugar, and cornstarch. The cornstarch marinade is a useful trick to help keep the pork from drying out when it gets cooked on that high heat. The sugar is just enough to create some caramelization for added flavor",
    "notes": "Tags: Main, Normal, pork loin, green onions",
    "title": "Pork Stir Fry with green Onion",
